  "prompt": "Which is the best DSLR under 2500?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, one of the best DSLRs under $2500 is the **Canon EOS 90D**. It offers excellent image quality, robust performance, and versatile features that make it suitable for both photography and videography. Here are some key features:\n\n- **32.5 Megapixel APS-C CMOS Sensor**: High-resolution image quality.\n- **4K Video**: Supports 4K video recording without crop.\n- **Dual Pixel CMOS AF**: Fast and accurate autofocus in live view and video.\n- **Weather-sealed body**: Durable and can withstand various shooting conditions.\n- **Optical Viewfinder with 45 cross-type AF points**: Good for fast and accurate focusing in challenging conditions.\n\nAnother great option in this price range is the **Nikon D7500**. It\u2019s a bit older but still highly regarded, especially for its low-light performance and speed. It has:\n\n- **20.9 Megapixel APS-C CMOS Sensor**: Great image quality and dynamic range.\n- **EXPEED 5 Image Processor**: Delivers high-speed processing and low-light capability.\n- **4K UHD Video Recording**: High-quality video capabilities.\n- **8 fps Continuous Shooting**: Good for action photography.\n- **Built-in Wi-Fi and Bluetooth**: Easy connectivity for sharing images.\n\nBoth of these models have their own strengths, so the choice depends on your specific needs and preferences. It's always a good idea to check the latest reviews and compare features to make the best decision.",
